{"_id":"05JW1rLyXQtScDkN","name":"Arcane Background (Miracles)","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p><b>Arcane Skill: </b>Faith (Spirit)</p><p><b>Starting Powers: </b>3</p><p><b>Power Points: </b>10</p><p>Those who invoke miracles draw their power from a divine presence of some sort, including gods, nature, or spirits. Their powers are usually invoked with a few words of prayer or by performing established rituals.</p><p>Those who cast miracles are champions of their particular religions. They typically have Hindrances that pertain to their service, such as Vow or Obligation. They might also have Connections to others of their religion who can help them out when their divine energies wane.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"10kE7H8N8q6CzrmU","name":"Humiliate","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Those with a cruel wit can destroy a rival's ego in a single remark or well-timed gesture. Your hero gets a free reroll on Taunt Tests.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Taunt d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"28BCZd6UASEAMRFb","name":"Menacing","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Being a brutish lout isn't always a drawback if you know how to use it. Menacing allows a character to put her bad looks or worse attitude to good use. The goon adds +2 to her Intimidation rolls.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, any one of Bloodthirsty, Mean, Ruthless, or Ugly"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"2BY74wa7oGD3z86C","name":"Fervor","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>A simple phrase uttered by a great leader can sometimes have momentous results. A commander with this ability can inspire his troops to bloody fervor by yelling a motto, slogan, or other inspirational words.</p><p>Extras in range add +1 to their Fighting damage rolls.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Spirit d8+, Command"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"35btRtggGhT6T9cI","name":"Chi","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your hero's martial arts training goes beyond the norm and into the realm of the mystical. At the start of each combat encounter, she gains a ”Chi Point” that can be spent to:</p><list><li>Reroll one of her failed attacks (even a Critical Failure).</li><li>Make an enemy discard an attack against her, then reroll it from scratch.</li><li>Add +d6 damage to a successful Fighting attack made with her hands, feet, claws, or other Natural Weapons (this may Ace).</li></list><p>Unspent Chi is lost at the end of the combat encounter.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Martial Warrior"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"3NOsRef34YsRd55Q","name":"Provoke","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Clever characters can manipulate their foes, drawing enemy focus on themselves to protect their allies. Once per turn, when your hero uses Taunt for a Test and gets a raise (see <b>Test </b>), she may Provoke the foe.</p><p>In addition to all the usual effects of the success and raise, the enemy suffers a -2 penalty to affect any other target besides the one who provoked her. This stacks with Distracted but not further instances of Provoke.</p><p>Provoke lasts until a Joker is drawn, someone else Provokes the target, or the encounter ends. Provoke can affect multiple targets, and may be combined with <b>Rabble Rouser </b>.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Taunt d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"5wMrOKhafx6EQTZI","name":"Command","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Command is the basic ability to give clear instructions and support to allies in the thick of battle. Extras in Command Range add +1 to their Spirit rolls when attempting to recover from being Shaken and Vigor when attempting to recover from being Stunned.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6EiqER9GITeW9D3X","name":"Attractive","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>It's no secret people are more willing to help those they find physically attractive. Your character adds +1 to Performance and Persuasion rolls if the target is attracted to his general type (gender, sex, species, etc.).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6SP8M7H4IYoQ828Z","name":"Calculating","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>A few seconds to study your foe's actions gives your hero a major advantage. When his Action Card is a Five or less, he ignores up to 2 points of penalties on one action that turn, which can include Multi-Action, cover, Range, and even Wound penalties.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6sih8tUZppD7Y72m","name":"Artificer","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Those who tangle with supernatural forces sometimes find ways to imbue powers into items. They may turn an ordinary blade into a magic sword, grant powerful potions to their friends, or even bless holy relics with divine grace.</p><p>Artificers can create <b>Arcane Devices </b>and give them to their allies.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any)"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8Oj41YAIvnwDqp6r","name":"Scavenger","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Once per encounter the hero may find, “suddenly remember,” or dig up some muchneeded piece of equipment, a handful of ammunition, or some other useful device.</p><p>The Game Master decides what constitutes an encounter, and has the final word on what can and can't be found.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Luck"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8RLSLKfBjImfCH5O","name":"Streetwise","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Streetwise characters know how to find the local black market, fence stolen goods, avoid the local law (or criminal element!), lay low when the heat’s on, obtain illegal weapons, find out which “boss” is hiring muscle, or similar shady activities</p><p>Streetwise characters add +2 to Intimidation or Persuasion rolls made to <b>Network </b>with shady or criminal elements. They also add +2 to Common Knowledge rolls pertaining to the types of disreputable activities listed above.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8Ysnwfh9j7o9P2mQ","name":"Brawler","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>His fists hit like hammers or his talons cut like scythes. His body feels like it's made of stone. Brawlers increase their Toughness by 1 and roll Strength +d4 when hitting with their fists or feet (or claws if they have them). If they already have a damage die from <b>Claws </b>, the Martial Artist Edge, etc., increase the damage die type by one instead.</p><p>The Brawler Edge doesn't make the character's fists <b>Natural Weapons </b>.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8nOW5zqxypJJJDTt","name":"Fleet-Footed","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The hero's Pace is increased by +2 and his running die increases one step (from d6 to d8, for example).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9KzcUGMqXJmhqwFr","name":"Brawny","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your bruiser is very large or very fit. Her Size increases by +1 (and therefore Toughness by 1) and she treats her Strength as one die type higher when determining <b>Encumbrance </b>and <b>Minimum Strength </b>to use armor, weapons, and equipment without a penalty.</p><p>Brawny can't increase a character's Size above +3.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9UxYHe8EXXtsySVb","name":"Arcane Background (Gifted)","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p><b>Arcane Skill: </b>Focus (Spirit)</p><p><b>Starting Powers: </b>1</p><p><b>Power Points: </b>15</p><p>The character has innate abilities that don't fit into the usual tropes of magic, miracles, or psionics. Their powers may be low-level super powers, divine gifts, or even alien abilities, and are often very unusual or unique for their setting.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"A0G91HR1uCWqYg6N","name":"Filthy Rich","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>This fortunate individual is very wealthy. He has five times the starting funds for the setting during character creation and, if appropriate, a yearly income after responsibilities of around $500,000.</p><p>Even wealthier characters may exist, but unless there's a game effect it probably shouldn't matter. This should be worked out with the GM and come with many more assets as well as onerous responsibilities.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Rich"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ALNsUNuRS5fK7idB","name":"Improved Frenzy","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>A character with Frenzy rolls a second Fighting die with any two of his Fighting attacks for the turn. Extra dices may be allocated to the same or different targets as he sees fit. Resolve each separately.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Frenzy"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"BLYto6zbNgMQmFWp","name":"Feint","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>When performing a <b>Test </b>with the Fighting skill, you can choose to make the foe resist with Smarts instead of Agility.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"BT2EjK1qi0dlOdUc","name":"Quick","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Quick characters have lightning-fast reflexes and a cool head. Whenever you are dealt an Action Card of Five or lower, you may discard it and draw again until you get a card higher than Five.</p><p>Characters with both the Level Headed and Quick Edges first draw their additional card and choose which to take. If that card is a Five or less, the Quick Edge may be used to draw a replacement until it's Six or higher.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"D1X0vGJk3NLB3Itv","name":"Master","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The character has mastered particular skill or attribute (his choice). This increases the Trait and its limit two steps (a d12+1 becomes a d12+3, for example). This Edge may be selected once per Trait.</p><p>In addition character's Wild Die increases to a d10 when rolling the selected Expert Trait.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary, Expert in affected Trait"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"DPz7Q0wg3IhXKW6c","name":"Hold the Line!","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Hold the Line strengthens the will of any Extras under the hero's command, adding +1 to their Toughness.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Command"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"DaF4501dmIfCERZZ","name":"First Strike","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Once per round, as long as he's not Shaken or Stunned, the hero gets a free Fighting attack against a foe immediately after he moves into Reach. (See <b>Free Attacks </b>).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ECjixhryUjUgB1AW","name":"Killer Instinct","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>This hero hates losing. He gets a free reroll in any opposed Test he initiates.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"FMFG97gtPY7TTHu3","name":"Channeling","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>When the character gets a raise on her arcane skill roll (or roll to activate or use an arcane device), she reduces its Power Point cost by 1. This <i>can </i>take it to 0.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any)"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"FY74lYTBK2sh9Hti","name":"No Mercy","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>When this killer spends a Benny to reroll damage, he adds +2 to his final total.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"FgBhja1h8YgtcZLB","name":"Natural Leader","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>This leader has proven herself time and time again, gaining the respect of all those who fight by her side.</p><p>Any Leadership Edge that says it applies only to Extras now applies to Wild Cards as well.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d8+, Command"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Fnlm4kRxPXDHJkHg","name":"Power Surge","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The character recovers 10 Power Points when his Action Card is a Joker. This may not exceed his usual limit.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Arcane Background (Any), arcane skill d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Gs0ep9s1S9OYcTaD","name":"Professional","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The character is an expert at a particular skill or attribute (his choice). This increases the Trait and its limit one step (a d12+1 becomes a d12+2, for example). This Edge may be selected once per Trait.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, maximum die type possible in affected Trait"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"GuzCHFoNRHNAVbJh","name":"Beast Master","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Animals take to your hero quickly and easily. They won’t attack him unless he attacks them first or they’re enraged for some reason.</p><p>The Beast Master’s “animal magnetism” is so great he’s attracted a loyal animal of some sort as well. This is typically an animal of Size 0 or smaller, subject to the GM’s approval.</p><p>The beast is an Extra and doesn’t Advance in Rank or abilities. If a pet is dismissed or killed, the hero gains a replacement in 1d4 days.</p><p><b>More Powerful Companions: </b>Beast Master may be taken more than once. Choose one of the effects below each time it's chosen:</p><list><li>Gain an additional pet.</li><li>Increase one of the pet's Traits one die type (only one Trait per pet).</li><li>Increase the maximum Size pet you may have by +1, to a maximum of 3.</li><li>Make one pet a Wild Card. (The hero must be of Heroic Rank).</li></list>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"HqKEQNlSg4IBHpyf","name":"Sidekick","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>A character who triumphs over evil time and time again becomes an inspiration to others. Eventually, one of these young crusaders may attempt to join the hero in his epic quests.</p><p>The hero gains a Novice Rank sidekick. The sidekick is a Wild Card, starts each session with two Bennies, may Advance, and has abilities that complement his mentor. The player character controls his sidekick just like any other ally, though he may occasionally cause trouble by getting captured, running into danger when he's not supposed to, and so on. The player should be prepared for his Edge to occasionally become a Hindrance!</p><p>If the sidekick dies, he isn't replaced unless the hero chooses this Edge again. Fortunately, heroes may always spend Bennies for their sidekicks as if she had the Common Bond Edge. Sidekicks must actually take that Edge to do the same for their mentors.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"J3Vvznt6guVcMUfM","name":"Rock and Roll!","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Experienced shooters learn to compensate for the recoil of fully automatic weapons. If a character with this Edge doesn't move on his turn, he ignores the Recoil penalty when firing at a Rate of Fire of 2 or higher. (See <b>Recoil </b>).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Shooting d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"JO47JtegpKogazra","name":"Dodge","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The hero can anticipate attacks or move erratically under fire. Unless the victim of a surprise attack and taken completely unaware, Dodge subtracts 2 from all ranged attacks made against the character. Dodge does <i>not </i>stack with actual cover, however.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"JvG2caGgACu2swDQ","name":"Martial Warrior","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The warrior is well on her way to becoming a martial arts master. When unarmed, she adds +2 to Fighting attacks and does Str+d6 damage (or increases her damage two die types if she already has it from another source, such as Claws or the Brawler Edge). She also ignores the Unarmed Defender rule.</p><p>The warrior is well on her way to becoming a martial arts master. Her fists and feet are weapons (see <b>Natural Weapons </b>) so she's always considered armed. She adds +2 when striking with them and causes Strength+d6 damage. If she already has a Strength damage die from the <b>Claws </b>racial ability or the Brawler Edge, increase the damage two die types.</p><p>Martial Artist does <i>not </i>add to damage from other Natural Weapons such as fangs or horns.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Martial Artist"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"KE5fIHFw0ekyfLs0","name":"Inspire","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Exceptional leaders inspire those around them to great feats of valor and determination. Once per turn, the hero may roll his Battle skill to Support one type of Trait roll, and apply it to <i>all </i>allied Extras in Command Range. A leader could Support all Shooting attacks in range, for example, or all Spirit rolls to recover from being Shaken.</p><p>Inspire is an action and requires some sort of communication with those it affects.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"M44aKwrX3YUalxdL","name":"Common Bond","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Selfless heroes and determined leaders know their greatest strength often comes from their companions, and are willing to give some of their own fortune, fate, or luck to support them.</p><p>A character with this Edge may freely give her Bennies to any other character she can communicate with. The player should explain what form this takes, from a quick shout of encouragement to a welcome pat on the back.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"My805lbNirkzzFDy","name":"Marksman","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The hero is a natural with ranged weapons. If she doesn’t move in a turn and fires no more than a Rate of Fire of 1 as her first action, she may add +1 to an Athletics (throwing) or Shooting roll, or ignore up to 2 points of penalties from Called Shots, Cover, Range, Scale, or Speed. This is a lesser version of the Aim maneuver and does not stack with it. Marksman doesn’t apply to additional attacks after the first.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Athletics d8+ or Shooting d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NwDP2v8ephl5WZy0","name":"Charismatic","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your hero is likable for some reason. She may be trustworthy or kind, or might just exude confidence and goodwill. You get one free reroll on Persuasion rolls.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"NzXlyYYgiszDigJi","name":"Retort","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>This verbal duelist can turn the slings and arrows of social combat right back at the unwitting fools who hurled them.</p><p>If a character with Retort gets a raise when resisting an Intimidation or Taunt Test, the <i>foe </i>is Distracted.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Taunt d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"O1Mp1wQxVZvemPMs","name":"Beast Bond","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Some individuals have an extraordinary bond with their animal companions. These characters may spend their own Bennies for any animals under their control, including mounts, pets, familiars, and so on.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ONx9cGIhIoRqLMbx","name":"Reliable","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>People know they can depend on your hero when they need assistance. He gets a free reroll on any Support roll.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Of9dkGJO6RJ74S40","name":"Luck","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The adventurer seems to be blessed by fate, karma, the gods, or whatever external forces he believes in (or believe in him!).</p><p>He draws one extra Benny at the beginning of each game session, allowing him to succeed at important tasks more often than most, and survive incredible dangers.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"P1DIyaP921ZHdcrl","name":"Counterattack","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Fighters with this Edge deal instant punishment for an enemy's mistakes. Once per round (if not Shaken or Stunned), the character receives a <b>Free Attack </b>against one failed Fighting attack against him. The counterattack takes place immediately (before other hits against the hero on the same Action Card, if any).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"PvLYyx0mqxY99BXq","name":"Improved Counterattack","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Fighters with this Edge deal instant punishment for an enemy's mistakes. Each round (if not Shaken or Stunned), the character receives a <b>Free Attack </b>against up to three failed Fighting attacks against him. The counterattack takes place immediately (before other hits against the hero on the same Action Card, if any).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Counterattack"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Px1GMEr3w2U4P7ee","name":"Mr. Fix It","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The mechanic adds +2 to Repair rolls. With a raise, he halves the time normally required to fix something. This means if a particular Repair job says a raise repairs it in half the time, a Mr. Fix It can finish the job in onequarter the time with a raise.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Repair d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Q5jOKKgcv9DEdvdz","name":"Improved Nerves of Steel","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your hero has learned to fight on through the most intense pain. He may ignore 2 point of Wound penalties.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Nerves of Steel"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"SP6wB36YvO9Wx7bD","name":"Brute","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Brutes focus on core strength and fitness over coordination and flexibility. They treat Athletics as linked to Strength instead of Agility for purposes of Advancement. The character may also resist Athletics Tests with Strength if she chooses.</p><p>Finally, Brutes increase the Short Range of any thrown item by +1. Double that for the adjusted Medium Range, and double again for Long Range. If a thrown item's Range is 3/6/12, for example, a Brute's Range is 4/8/16.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"SsqyYMXGnX51alwf","name":"Arcane Background (Magic)","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p><b>Arcane Skill: </b>Spellcasting (Smarts)</p><p><b>Starting Powers: </b>3</p><p><b>Power Points: </b>10</p><p>Magicians range from powerful wizards to vile cultists. They draw on raw supernatural energy to fuel their eldritch fires. This energy infuses the worlds in which they live, and is drawn forth with gestures, words of power, or ancient runes.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"U9PspvxdRGgulPS3","name":"Soldier","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Professional soldiers get used to carrying heavy loads, and enduring harsh conditions. After a few days getting used to their gear (GM's call), they treat their Strength as one die type higher when determining <b>Encumbrance </b>and <b>Minimum Strength </b>to use armor, weapons, and equipment without a penalty. (This stacks with the Brawny Edge.)</p><p>They also get a free reroll on Vigor rolls made to survive environmental hazards (see <b>Hazards </b>).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"UwN8Lsc4urEWst58","name":"Nerves of Steel","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your hero has learned to fight on through the most intense pain. He may ignore 1 point of Wound penalties.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"VLgT5RYASdAKzBL0","name":"Great Luck","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The adventurer seems to be blessed by fate, karma, the gods, or whatever external forces he believes in (or believe in him!).</p><p>He draws two extra Bennies at the beginning of each game session, allowing him to succeed at important tasks more often than most, and survive incredible dangers.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Luck"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"VdMBBSVAsNNGlqdV","name":"Gadgeteer","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Some mechanical gurus can build incredible devices out of most anything.</p><p>A Gadgeteer can spend up to three Power Points to “jury rig” a device from most any reasonable collection of spare parts. This allows her to use any power normally available to Weird Scientists of her Rank or lower in her particular setting, with a Power Point cost of 3 or lower.</p><p>The total cost of the power (plus any modifiers) cannot exceed the points spent to create it, but she may create multiple devices as long as she has the points to do so.</p><p>This takes one entire turn, during which she can do nothing else but make a Weird Science roll at -2 (she cannot take Multi-Actions that turn).</p><p>The inventor uses Power Points directly from her pool for the device, but once its initial Duration is finished (it cannot be maintained) it falls apart into its component pieces.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Weird Science), Weird Science d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"WDMb9R2ElBjnvgVU","name":"Ace","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Aces are pilots and drivers who have a special affinity with their car, boat, plane, or other vehicle. They ignore two points of penalties to any Boating, Driving, or Piloting roll, and may spend Bennies to Soak damage for any vehicle they control or command, using the appropriate Boating, Driving, or Piloting skill instead of Vigor. Each success and raise negates a Wound.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"WN5tXXxngN3vfYFH","name":"Improved Trademark Weapon","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The hero knows one unique weapon (Excalibur, Old Betsy, Sting) like the back of his hand. When using it, he adds +2 to his Athletics (throwing), Fighting, or Shooting rolls, and +2 to Parry when readied (even if it's a ranged weapon).</p><p>A fighter can take this Edge multiple times, applying it to a different weapon each time. If a Trademark Weapon is lost, he can replace it but the benefits don't kick in for a few days (however long the GM feels is dramatically appropriate).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Trademark Weapon"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"WVND7Wy39ZCDUbm4","name":"Acrobat","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The Acrobat gets one free reroll on Athletics totals that involve balance, tumbling, or grappling. It doesn't affect rolls to interrupt actions, climb, swim, or throw.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Athletics d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"WyRDSgT5tseJMf0C","name":"Improved Dodge","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The hero can anticipate attacks or move erratically under fire. Unless the victim of a surprise attack and taken completely unaware, Improved Dodge subtracts 2 from all ranged attacks made against the character. Improved Dodge does <i>not </i>stack with actual cover, however.</p><p>Also the hero adds +2 when Evading area effect attacks. See Evasion.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Dodge"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"XmBUBvyhhbw3l5vM","name":"Free Runner","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your character practices ”parkour” or is just very skilled at running, jumping, swinging, scampering up walls, and over obstacles.</p><p>As long as there are obstacles she can bound on, bounce off, or swing on, she moves at her full Pace on Difficult Ground when on foot. She also adds +2 to her Athletics rolls when climbing and in foot <b>Chases </b>.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Athletics d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"XrqOBcGZXDZo1H74","name":"Fast Healer","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Those with this blessing add +2 to Vigor rolls for natural healing, and check every three days instead of five (see <b>Healing </b>).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Y0BB24sAJGqcKnKu","name":"Command Presence","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>A booming voice, effective commands, natural charisma, or simple training results in a much more effective combat element. A hero with this Edge has a Command Range of 10” (20 yards).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Command"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"Y5c7gyHHrNQHw7o3","name":"Bolster","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Belittling or humiliating an enemy can also boost your ally's spirits. When this character successfully Tests a foe, he may also remove the <b>Distracted </b>or <b>Vulnerable </b>state from one of his allies.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"YSUzTyHGFtohUz78","name":"Steady Hands","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Firing from the back of a horse or moving vehicle is tricky business, but your adventurer has figured it out. She ignores the <b>Unstable Platform </b>penalty.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aAAIxn90ZCjjo7xf","name":"Harder to Kill","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your hero is tougher to kill than Rasputin. He may ignore his Wound penalties when making Vigor rolls to avoid <b>Bleeding Out </b>. If he is ever ”killed,” roll a die. On an odd result, he's dead as usual. On an even roll, he's Incapacitated but somehow escapes death. He may be captured, stripped of all his belongings, or mistakenly left for dead, but he somehow survives.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Hard to Kill"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aCPPBcGJpvh2BxCk","name":"Martial Artist","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The fighter has trained in basic martial arts. Her fists and feet are weapons (see <b>Natural Weapons </b>) so she's always considered armed. She adds +1 when striking with them and causes Strength+d4 damage. If she already has a Strength damage die from the <b>Claws </b>racial ability or the Brawler Edge, increase the damage a die type.</p><p>Martial Artist does <i>not </i>add to damage from other Natural Weapons such as fangs or horns.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"aXn42jdmtO0AKTlS","name":"Soul Drain","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Desperate times call for desperate measures. Soul Drain allows an arcane character to channel her physical energy into power, taking a level of Fatigue to recover up to five Power Points. She can take an additional level of Fatigue (to Exhaustion) to recover up to five more Power Points. She cannot render herself Incapacitated in this way.</p><p>Fatigue incurred by Soul Drain comes from deep within and may <i>only </i>be recovered naturally. The <i>relief </i>power and similar abilities have no effect.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any), arcane skill d10+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"b8c2XQRplWElNznp","name":"Liquid Courage","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>This gregarious individual processes alcohol far differently than most. The round after consuming a stiff drink (about eight ounces of hard liquor or equivalent), her Vigor increases one die type (increasing Toughness as well). The drinker can also ignore one level of Wound penalties (which stacks with other abilities that do the same).</p><p>Smarts, Agility, and all linked skills suffer a -1 penalty for the duration, however.</p><p>The effect lasts for one hour after it begins, at which point the boozer suffers a level of Fatigue for the next four hours.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"bgXshf6HbC9Y1qQp","name":"Famous","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your hero is truly famous. She's wellknown in a large circle such as a country, a large industry, or a popular medium (film or television, the music industry). She makes 5x the normal fee when performing and adds +2 to Persuasion rolls when influencing friendly individuals who know who she is.</p><p>The price is higher for the truly Famous, too, with more demands on her time, obligations, rivals, scandals, and an inability to operate in crowds without being recognized.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fame"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"d2559y5WeZvvCmxD","name":"Iron Will","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Self-confidence is powerful armor against those who attempt to attack this individual’s will. He adds +2 to his total when resisting Tests with Smarts or Spirit.</p><p>Also the hero now adds +2 to resist powers and negate their effects. Iron Will doesn’t stack with Brave, nor does it apply to subsequent rolls resulting from powers such as being Shaken by a damaging power, fear, or the like.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strong Willed"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"d4K6MvoE4wFADFF4","name":"Power Points","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Wizards, weird scientists, and other arcane types always want more power. This Edge grants them an additional 5 Power Points. Power Points may be selected more than once, but only once per Rank. It may be taken as often as desired at Legendary Rank, but each grants only 2 additional points.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Any)"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"dX2bji2XWieqa6Jg","name":"Scholar","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Learned professors, devoted students, and amateur enthusiasts spend great amounts of time and energy studying particular subjects. They become experts in these fields, and rarely fail to answer questions in their particular area of expertise.</p><p>Pick any one of the following skills: Academics, Battle, Occult, Science, or a Smarts-based ”knowledge”-type skill allowed in your setting, and add +2 to the total whenever they're used.</p><p>This Edge may be taken more than once if applied to different skills.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Research d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"dwRDhF3FVi2dvapP","name":"Alertness","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Not much gets by this hero. He's very observant and perceptive, and adds +2 to his Notice rolls to hear, see, or otherwise sense the world around him.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"eGS1Fg9keIV7N0Ar","name":"Improved Block","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Through hard-fought experience your hero has learned to defend himself in vicious hand-to-hand combat. His Parry increases by +2 and any Gang Up bonus against him is reduced by two.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Block"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"eah9IzxN4kxEUCOX","name":"Arcane Resistance","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Magic and the supernatural hold little sway with this individual. Whether by nature, heritage, or training he's particularly resistant to magic, psionics, weird science, and other supernatural energies.</p><p>Arcane skills targeting the hero suffer a -2 penalty (even if cast by allies!) and magical damage is reduced by 2 as well.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ecwCiR9dCh2rPM5z","name":"Healer","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>A hero with this Edge adds +2 to all Healing rolls, whether natural or magical in nature.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"eqBpKoHZ8H3IrzTx","name":"Improved Level Headed","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Fighters who can keep their cool when everyone else is running for cover make deadly combatants. A hero with this Edge draws two additional Action Cards in combat and chooses which to use.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Level Headed"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"fghnwCSc7fnMFadQ","name":"Elan","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Elan means energy or spirit. Those who have it rise to the occasion when the going gets toughest. When you spend a Benny to reroll a Trait, add +2 to the total. The bonus applies only when rerolling. It doesn't apply to damage rolls (since they're not Trait rolls), nor does it apply to Soak rolls unless you're using <i>another </i>Benny to reroll the Vigor check.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"g73Tq70QjBKoKlMA","name":"Hard To Kill","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>This adventurer has more lives than a herd of cats. He may ignore his Wound penalties when making Vigor rolls to avoid <b>Bleeding Out </b>.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"gfFOT8JEAjPfqd9B","name":"Extra Effort","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Some Gifted can dig deep into their souls to significantly boost their powers.</p><p>Extra Effort increases a Focus total after it's rolled by +1 for 1 Power Point, or +2 for 3 Power Points. It may not be used to improve a Critical Failure.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Gifted), Focus d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"gyJNCYwoRMFgsueZ","name":"Combat Acrobat","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The tumbler leaps quickly about so that attacks against her are made at -1 as long as she's aware of the attack, can reasonably move about, and isn't suffering any Encumbrance or Minimum Strength penalties.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Acrobat"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hLFCMFxMJAhDyUw0","name":"Extraction","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>When a character withdraws from melee, adjacent attackers get a free Fighting attack against him (see <b>Withdrawing from Melee </b>). This is a very dangerous proposition for most, but not your wily champion.</p><p>When moving away from adjacent foes, one of them (player's choice), doesn't get his free Fighting attack.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"hZQTjX7lb7GmO0Yp","name":"Danger Sense","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your hero can sense when something bad is about to happen. When rolling for <b>Surprise </b>, he adds +2 to his Notice roll to act in the first round. With a raise, he starts the encounter on Hold.</p><p>In other situations not covered by the Surprise rules (a sniper shot, pit trap, poisoned drink, etc.), Danger Sense gives him a Notice roll at -2 (or +2 if a Notice roll is usually allowed) to detect the hazard and take appropriate action. If this was an attack and the hero makes his Notice roll, the foe doesn't get The Drop against him.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"iT7UR7f4FxZKdJyp","name":"Improved First Strike","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>As long as he's not Shaken or Stunned, the hero gets a free Fighting attack against up to three foes immediately after they move into Reach. (See <b>Free Attacks </b>).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Heroic, First Strike"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"jpjuYIUBFWDnvzqj","name":"Rapid Fire","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The shooter is practiced at taking quick and accurate shots. As long as she's armed with a fast-firing ranged weapon of some sort (such as a revolver or semi-automatic) and has enough ammunition to do so, she may increase her weapon's Rate of Fire by 1 for any one of her Shooting attacks that turn.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Shooting d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"k9r3BZnpHYeqXxAy","name":"Arcane Background (Weird Science)","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p><b>Arcane Skill: </b>Weird Science (Smarts)</p><p><b>Starting Powers: </b>2</p><p><b>Power Points: </b>15</p><p>Weird scientists use strange and powerful inventions beyond the normal technological level of the setting. Such creations might be possible due to super fuels, alien discoveries, or the raw intellect of rare super-geniuses who push the boundaries of science.</p><p>A weird scientist’s <b>Trappings </b>must always include the item they’re associated with. The <i>burst </i>power might manifest through a magical flamethrower in <i>Deadlands: The Weird West </i>, for instance, while “Dr. Gabriel’s Wondrous Restorative Elixir!” is a <i>healing </i>potion.</p><p>Weird scientists must have their devices at hand to activate their powers (but see <b>Jury Rig </b>, below).</p><p>Other characters can’t activate the inventor’s creations. They might not understand the strange mechanisms required to make it work, the device might not be “calibrated” or portioned for other users, or it might just “fritz out” for anyone but the creator. While this may seem a bit strange narratively, the “magic”—and the Power Points—come from the inventor so he must be the one to activate it.</p><p>Creating devices for others is possible—it just requires an <b>Arcane Device </b>and the <b>Artificer </b>Edge.</p><p>The inventor can <i>use </i>his devices on others, of course, including administering drinks from his magical elixirs or giving them injections of some miraculous super serum he’s created. If Dr. Gabriel administers his elixir, for example, he rolls to activate the power normally. If he <i>gives </i>someone the bottle to use later, they’ll find it’s lost its potency.</p><p><b>Jury Rig: </b>Weird scientists must usually activate their powers through their assigned device, but they can improvise other ways if needed at a -2 penalty. This requires a decent rationale relative to the setting and the GM’s permission.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kG5zyhr8V9DVppxx","name":"Improved Rapid Fire","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The shooter is practiced at taking quick and accurate shots. As long as she's armed with a fast-firing ranged weapon of some sort (such as a revolver or semi-automatic) and has enough ammunition to do so, she may increase her weapon's Rate of Fire by 1 for any two of her Shooting attacks that turn.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Rapid Fire"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kbJ3CTNR3dDGIuHZ","name":"Combat Reflexes","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your warrior recovers quickly from shock and trauma. He adds +2 to his rolls when attempting to recover from being Shaken or Stunned.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"kkEPLQhD1pK5JaBJ","name":"Dead Shot","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>When your Action Card is a Joker, double the total damage of your first successful Athletics (throwing) or Shooting roll this round.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Athletics or Shooting d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"lNyYhLWiR6I7C5ap","name":"Rapid Recharge","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Power Points normally recharge at a rate of 5 points every hour spent resting (see <b>Recharging </b>). This Edge increases that rate to 10 every hour.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d6+, Arcane Background (Any)"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"lmhwNsY3cvRNN1id","name":"Followers","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Each time this Edge is chosen, five followers come to fight by the hero's side. If any are lost, others eventually take their place (how long is up to the GM and the circumstances).</p><p>Followers must be cared for and generally want a share of whatever loot, treasure, or other rewards the hero acquires. Otherwise, they are completely dedicated to their task. They won't throw their lives away but are willing to risk them repeatedly in his service.</p><p>Use the <b>Soldier </b>profile for the followers. A hero may outfit her allies as she sees fit. Followers <b>Advance </b>just like player characters.</p><p>Use the <b>Allies </b>rules to give them distinctive personalities if desired.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Legendary"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"mnEFcIixhrzTzLpL","name":"Investigator","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Investigators spend a great deal of time researching ancient legends, working the streets, or deducing devilish mysteries. Some of these heroes are actual private investigators while others are sleuthing mages in a fantasy world or inquisitive college professors stumbling upon Things Man Was Not Meant to Know.</p><p>Investigators add +2 to Research rolls and Notice rolls made to search through desks for important papers, sift through stacks of junk mail for something of note, or spy obscured items from piles of junk or debris.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Research d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"moFo64qd9ptpFRfq","name":"Mentalist","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Constant contact with multiple minds gives these psionic agents an edge when it comes to forcing or resisting mental assaults.</p><p>Mentalists add +2 to opposed Psionics rolls, whether they are using their powers against a foe or defending against a rival.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Psionics), Psionics d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"nhVIanElBWJbwf9e","name":"Block","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Through hard-fought experience your hero has learned to defend himself in vicious hand-to-hand combat. His Parry increases by +1 and any Gang Up bonus against him is reduced by one.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"ni6OHkFnnK3uwtQ1","name":"Concentration","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Through training and focus, the caster is extremely efficient in channeling arcane forces. The base Duration of any non-Instant power is doubled. This includes maintaining powers as well.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Any)"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"nimWfM1D47oV6BuX","name":"Rich","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Whether the individual was born with a silver spoon in his mouth or earned it through hard work, he's got more money than most.</p><p>Rich heroes start with three times the normal starting funds for the setting. If a regular income is appropriate for this setting, the hero receives the modern-day equivalent of a $150,000 annual salary.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"oGsgP3Q7MKjmh7SS","name":"Aristocrat","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>This individual was born into privilege or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the Rich or Filthy Rich Edge), but she still walks in the elite social circles of the setting.</p><p>Aristocrats add +2 to Persuasion when <b>Networking </b>with the local elite, captains of industry, nobles, or other aristocrats. They also add +2 to Common Knowledge rolls made to know the etiquette of the upper class, recognize family trees or heraldry, or recall gossip concerning others of their station.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"oo6hFapO8qXhshh2","name":"Bruiser","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>His fists hit like hammers or his talons cut like scythes. His body feels like it's made of stone. Brawlers increase their Toughness by 2 and roll Strength +d6 when hitting with their fists or feet (or claws if they have them). If they already have a damage die from <b>Claws </b>, the Martial Artist Edge, etc., increase the damage die type by two instead.</p><p>The Brawler Edge doesn't make the character's fists <b>Natural Weapons </b>.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Brawler"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"oypDxQ08qRiyl8HK","name":"McGyver","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>A McGyver can improvise a device from common resources when the need arises. Given a few simple items, he can make a Repair roll to craft improvised weapons, explosives, or tools, that last until used or the end of the encounter (GM's call). This takes one entire turn, and he can't move or take any other actions while constructing the device.</p><p>Failure means the device isn't ready. A Critical Failure means he doesn't have the right materials and can't create the device this encounter.</p><p>Success creates a minor explosive (2d4 explosive in a Small Blast Template), a one shot projectile weapon like a “zip gun” (Range 5/10/20, Damage 2d6), rickety raft, electrical source, etc.</p><p>A raise creates a larger explosive (2d6 in a Medium Blast Template or 2d4 in a Large), a better ranged weapon (five shots, 2d8 damage, Range 10/20/40), a more stable raft, a more powerful battery, etc.</p><p>The quality or power of the creation is completely up to the Game Master, but creativity should be rewarded, particularly in the most dire and dramatic situations.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Notice d8+, Repair d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"pj54exxaC58urQoB","name":"Iron Jaw","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The hero can shrug off even extreme blows. He adds +2 to Soak rolls and Vigor rolls to avoid <b>Knockout Blows </b>.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Vigor d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"qAQP7EnWZZVmz1rH","name":"Improved Rapid Recharge","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Power Points normally recharge at a rate of 5 points every hour spent resting (see <b>Recharging </b>). This Edge increases that rate to 20 every hour.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Rapid Recharge"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"qQLCxyshJFABAhTy","name":"Champion","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Champions are holy (or unholy) men and women chosen to fight for a particular deity or religion. Most are pious souls ready and willing to lay down their lives for a greater cause, but some may have been born into the role and follow their path with some reluctance.</p><p>Champions fight the forces of darkness (or good), adding +2 damage when attacking supernaturally evil (or good if they're evil) creatures. The bonus applies to area effect damage, ranged attacks, powers, etc.</p><p>The GM must decide which foes this bonus applies to, but generally it's any evil (or good!) creature born of magic or with any supernatural abilities.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Fighting d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"qh8NO7bdC3ALlNPt","name":"Improvisational Fighter","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Heroes often find themselves fighting with pieces of equipment or furnishings not designed for combat. A brawler with this Edge has a knack for using such improvised weapons. He ignores the usual –2 penalty when wielding them. See <b>Improvised Weapons </b>.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"rUSxwvQ31nWkenJG","name":"Expert","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The character is an expert at a particular skill or attribute (his choice). This increases the Trait and its limit two steps (a d12+1 becomes a d12+3, for example). This Edge may be selected once per Trait.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Professional in affected Trait"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"raTWTXZN3OStxlKW","name":"Improved Arcane Resistance","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Magic and the supernatural hold little sway with this individual. Whether by nature, heritage, or training he's particularly resistant to magic, psionics, weird science, and other supernatural energies.</p><p>Arcane skills targeting the hero suffer a -4 penalty (even if cast by allies!) and magical damage is reduced by 4 as well.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Resistance"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"rcYrQ8oxpBVegHSx","name":"Assassin","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Assassins are trained killers who know how to kill even the toughest foes. They add +2 to damage rolls when their foe is Vulnerable or they have The Drop.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Fighting d6+, Stealth d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"sAOOnV66tfS2aGPU","name":"Ambidextrous","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your warrior is as deft with his left hand as he is with his right. He ignores the <b>Off-Hand </b>penalty.</p><p>If holding a weapon in each hand, Ambidextrous characters may stack Parry bonuses (if any) from both weapons.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"snXjWT73w3X8Mcf1","name":"Linguist","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>This world-traveler has an ear for languages. She begins play knowing half her Smarts die type in different Language skills of her choice at d6 (see the <b>Language </b>skill).</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"t6i93OII7HbT6hA0","name":"Master Tactician","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The commander has a natural grasp of small unit tactics and can take advantage of rapidly changing situations.</p><p>A Tactician is dealt two extra Action Cards each round of combat or a chase—kept separate from his own cards. At the start of the round, he may discard or give them to any two allied Extra in Command Range. The player or GM controlling the receiving character can decide whether to accept and replace her current Action Card, or discard it.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Tactician"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"tffE8gB2RKTpfGer","name":"Double Tap","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Experienced firearms experts fire two shots in rapid succession without spoiling their aim.</p><p>Double Tap can only be used with weapons that have a Rate of Fire of 1 and can fire two shots without needing to manually reload. It adds +1 to hit and damage at the cost of one extra bullet. This is per action, so a shooter can Double Tap more than once if she performs a Multi-Action.</p><p>Double Tap <i>cannot </i>be combined with Rapid Fire.</p><p>If used with a weapon capable of <b>Three Round Burst </b>, it adds +2 to Shooting and damage instead of +1 and expends <i>six </i>bullets.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Shooting d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"tvFAoB6hcoQ2Rim8","name":"Connections","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your heroine is connected to people or organizations who can help her when the chips are down. It might be the mob, the Feds, a union, or even other adventurers. Connections may be taken more than once, selecting a new faction or contact each time. Once per session, and assuming she can get in touch with them, the heroine can call on her friends for a favor.</p><p>The favor depends on the nature of the contact (GM's call), but might include a loan, gear, a few allied fighters, transportation, information, or even a professional with critical skills the party doesn't have, like a hacker or scholar.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"uDLOKrmCKZOgr9tw","name":"New Power","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>An arcane character may learn two new powers by choosing this Edge (which may be taken multiple times). He may choose from any powers of his Rank or lower normally available to his particular Arcane Background.</p><p>A character can add a new Trapping on a power she already has instead of gaining a new one. She might add an ice Trapping to her existing fire bolt, for example, so she could switch between ice and fire Trappings freely.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Arcane Background (Any)"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"uNtNVsueVFncLxrA","name":"Arcane Background (Psionics)","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p><b>Arcane Skill: </b>Psionics (Smarts)</p><p><b>Starting Powers: </b>3</p><p><b>Power Points: </b>10</p><p>Psionicists tap into their own mental energy to manipulate matter, read minds, and far more. Some are agents in the employ of a vast government agency, while others are often on the run from them! Some may have years of training or they might have developed their incredible powers in isolation.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Sweep","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Sweep allows a character to make a single Fighting attack and apply it against all targets in his Reach at a -2 penalty (friends and foes alike). Resolve damage separately for each enemy that's hit.</p><p>A fighter may only perform a Sweep once per turn. It may not be combined with Frenzy.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"unOeGUPFq9rcPVOP"}
{"_id":"uoyWpb858DWofwXR","name":"Giant Killer","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The bigger they are, the harder they are to kill. At least for most. Your hero knows how to find the weak points in the most massive of foes.</p><p>He adds +1d6 damage when attacking creatures who are three or more Sizes larger than himself (see <b>Size </b>). A human (Size 0) gets the bonus against a creature of Size 3 or greater.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vI3qcsheFNN10hN4","name":"Frenzy","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>A character with Frenzy rolls a second Fighting die with any one of his Fighting attacks for the turn. The extra die may be allocated to the same or different targets as he sees fit. Resolve each separately.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vV8G97THN5v5mC0A","name":"Improved Extraction","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>When a character withdraws from melee, adjacent attackers get a free Fighting attack against him (see <b>Withdrawing from Melee </b>). This is a very dangerous proposition for most, but not your wily champion.</p><p>When moving away from adjacent foes, up to three of them (player's choice), doesn't get the free Fighting attack.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Extraction"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"vY0Tw7AAzMLIEw70","name":"Level Headed","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Fighters who can keep their cool when everyone else is running for cover make deadly combatants. A hero with this Edge draws an additional Action Card in combat and chooses which to use.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"w70c5651reedFWkJ","name":"Rabble Rouse","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>This instigator knows how to rile up several enemies at once.</p><p>Once per turn, a character with this Edge can make a social <b>Test </b>with Intimidation or Taunt against all enemies in a Medium Blast Template. The targets must be able to see and hear the hero clearly. Each defender resists and is affected by the <b>Test </b>separately.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"whk7iA29VrHdaztE","name":"Berserk","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Berserkers become wild and nearly uncontrollable when the ”red rage” takes them, but they are deadly killing machines as well!</p><p>Immediately after suffering a Wound or a Shaken result (from physical damage only), your hero must make a Smarts roll or go Berserk. She <i>can </i>voluntarily fail this check if she likes.</p><p>Going Berserk has the following effects:</p><list><li><b>Fury: </b>The character's Strength increases a die type and every melee attack must be a <b>Wild Attack </b>. She cannot use any skills that require wit or concentration (GM's call). She may scream out threats and use Intimidation, for example.</li><li><b>Enraged: </b>Adrenaline and rage fuel the berserker's muscles, adding +2 to Toughness. She ignores one level of Wound penalties (this stacks with any other abilities that reduce Wound penalties).</li><li><b>Reckless Abandon: </b>Anytime a berserker rolls a Critical Failure on a Fighting check, she hits a random target within range of her attack ( <i>not </i>the intended target), friend or foe. If there are no applicable targets, the blow simply misses, smashes nearby objects, etc.</li></list><p>After five consecutive rounds of berserk fury, the hero takes a level of Fatigue. At ten rounds, she takes another level of Fatigue and the rage ends. She may also <i>choose </i>to end her rage at any time by making a Smarts -2 roll (as a free action; possibly avoiding Fatigue if she manages to end her rage before it's incurred!). Start the count anew if she goes berserk again, even in the same battle.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"wwOVrQkJKP6O2IhF","name":"Master of Arms","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The warrior increases his Parry by +2 and the bonus damage die for Fighting rolls is a d10 instead of a d6 (see <b>Bonus Damage </b>). He must be armed to gain these benefits, but this includes the Martial Artist Edge, claws, or other abilities that count as weapons.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Legendary, Weapon Master"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"xepEXdxNCIAD3hjV","name":"Holy/Unholy Warrior","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Believers face grave dangers in service to their divine patrons. To survive such hardships, the forces of good (or evil) grant miracles and the ability to turn their favor into supernatural protection.</p><p>The chosen may add +1 to the total of a final Soak roll for each Power Point spent, to a maximum of 4.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (Miracles), Faith d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"yDZjsjg5hbLchCF1","name":"Brave","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Those with this Edge have learned to master their fear, or have dealt with so many horrors they've become jaded. These valiant explorers add +2 to Fear checks and subtract 2 from <b>Fear Table </b>results.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"yFStWNGkADVseKU6","name":"Strong Willed","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Self-confidence is powerful armor against those who attempt to attack this individual’s will. He adds +2 to his total when resisting Tests with Smarts or Spirit.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"yZSPaREZetAuxFSP","name":"Fame","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Your character is a minor celebrity of some sort. She might be a popular bard known in a particular fiefdom, a minor rock star, or a beloved B-movie actor.</p><p>She makes double the normal fee when performing for pay (see <b>Performance </b>. She can also use her celebrity to add +1 to Persuasion rolls if a target is friendly and knows who she is (a Common Knowledge roll modified by how likely the individual is to know the celebrity).</p><p>The downside of Fame is that the individual is often recognized, others frequently want something from her, she may be followed by fans or admirers, or she may not be able to shirk obligations, performances, or other duties without causing trouble for herself.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"yeuhz0PozBvGV1iB","name":"Improved Sweep","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Improved Sweep allows a character to make a single Fighting attack and apply it against all targets in his Reach (friends and foes alike). This version of the Edge ignores -2 penalty. Resolve damage separately for each enemy that's hit.</p><p>A fighter may only perform a Sweep once per turn. It may not be combined with Frenzy.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Veteran, Sweep"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"yoR9e4J66zUnNmzs","name":"Mighty Blow","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>If your Action Card is a Joker, double the damage of your first successful Fighting attack this round.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"zLn7PODvT3T88ube","name":"Jack-Of-All-Trades","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Through advanced schooling, book-learning, computer-enhanced skill programs, or just amazing intuitive perception, your hero has a talent for picking up skills on the fly. There's little he can't figure out given a little time and a dash of luck.</p><p>The character makes a Smarts roll as an action after observing or studying some subject. She gains a d4 in the relevant skill with success, or d6 with a raise. She may try again after an hour of study, trial and effort, or immersion if she fails or wants to try for a raise. This lasts until the character attempts to learn a different subject, whether she’s successful or not.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d10+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Tactician","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The commander has a natural grasp of small unit tactics and can take advantage of rapidly changing situations.</p><p>A Tactician is dealt an extra Action Card each round of combat or a chase—kept separate from his own cards. At the start of the round, he may discard it or give it to any one allied Extra in Command Range. The player or GM controlling the receiving character can decide whether to accept and replace her current Action Card, or discard it.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Command, Battle d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8n4NATs4Cvk69Onu"}
{"_id":"unOeGUPFq9rcPVOP","name":"Sweep","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Sweep allows a character to make a single Fighting attack and apply it against all targets in his Reach at a -2 penalty (friends and foes alike). Resolve damage separately for each enemy that's hit.</p><p>A fighter may only perform a Sweep once per turn. It may not be combined with Frenzy.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Fighting d8+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8n4NATs4Cvk69Onu","name":"Tactician","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>The commander has a natural grasp of small unit tactics and can take advantage of rapidly changing situations.</p><p>A Tactician is dealt an extra Action Card each round of combat or a chase—kept separate from his own cards. At the start of the round, he may discard it or give it to any one allied Extra in Command Range. The player or GM controlling the receiving character can decide whether to accept and replace her current Action Card, or discard it.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Smarts d8+, Command, Battle d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[]}
{"name":"Thief","permission":{"default":0,"89eyOdrISceMvDfi":3},"type":"edge","data":{"description":"<benefit type=”formattedtext”><p>Thieves specialize in deceit, treachery, and acrobatics. They can be invaluable where traps must be detected, walls must be climbed, and locks must be picked.</p><p>Thieves know how to use protrusions on walls and window ledges to climb the tallest of buildings, scampering through streets and back alleys like cats. They add +1 to Athletics rolls made to climb in urban areas.</p><p>Thieves also know how to use the dark areas between the streetlights of cities to conceal their movements, and add +1 to Stealth rolls when in an urban environment.</p><p>Finally, these rogues are—not surprisingly— adept at Thievery itself, adding +1 to those rolls in all circumstances.</p>","notes":"","additionalStats":[],"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Stealth d6+, Thievery d6+"}},"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"_id":"OjLMohRq3ywgDRpc"}
